    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_41241499" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/41241499" />
    <a title="Sidney" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1842024-sidney"><img alt="Sidney" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458385892p2/1842024.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/41241499?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sidney" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sidney" href="/user/show/1842024-sidney">Sidney</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780812509601" href="/book/show/1057766.Tales_from_Nightside">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer41241499" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11037249343783647584">This book is filled with subtle chills. Grant was an advocate of quiet horror, and you can see that form in practice here. Each story builds an eerie world and each has a deliberate and deep impact. Don’t come expecting explanations. These are tales of mystery and dark forces and characters who can’t escape them. Some of my favorites include Oxrun Station entries “Home” and “If Damon Comes,” “The Gentle Passing of a Hand” and the dark “The Three of Tens.” “Come Dance With Me On My Pony’s Grave” </span>
  <span id="freeText11037249343783647584" style="display:none">This book is filled with subtle chills. Grant was an advocate of quiet horror, and you can see that form in practice here. Each story builds an eerie world and each has a deliberate and deep impact. Don’t come expecting explanations. These are tales of mystery and dark forces and characters who can’t escape them. Some of my favorites include Oxrun Station entries “Home” and “If Damon Comes,” “The Gentle Passing of a Hand” and the dark “The Three of Tens.” “Come Dance With Me On My Pony’s Grave” is powerful as well. Read in the right frame of mind with the right amount of imagination, these are stunning. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11037249343783647584" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


